In [13]:
#if the most recent mean return is positive, then we should take short position minus one
#if the most recent mean return is negative, then we should take long position minus one
#we taking the contrarian or opposite position with that minus sign (-), when the most recent mean return is positive then our position is negative and vice versa.
#the minus sign also the different between contrarian and moementum strategy, if we take the minus sign it become momentum strategy
#as we could see, if the return are negative, position is positive and vice versa. which mean it contrarian, especialy when we do a return rolling which calculated the mean return of last 3 return and give us the mean of the return and then we taking a position accordingly 
data['position'] = -np.sign(data['returns'].rolling(window).mean()) #contrarian (minus sign)
data

In [25]:
#taking buy and hold return first
to_plot = ['returns']
In [27]:
#the purpose is to compere all the windows in one chart
#adding multiple windows 1,2,3,5,10
#so it would create new column in data which result in position and strategy for every given window we specify
for w in [1, 2, 3, 5, 10]:
    #menambahkan position dan strategy ke data varibale
    data['position{}'.format(w)] = -np.sign(data['returns'].rolling(w).mean()) #create a position for every windows
    data['strategy{}'.format(w)] = data['position{}'.format(w)].shift(1) * data['returns'] #create return strategy for every windows
    #menambahkan ke dalam to_plot list for visualization
    to_plot.append('strategy{}'.format(w)) #append the strategy to to_plot list

In [70]:
#create a half spread  by devided spread with 2, half spread is use when one trade (action) happen
half_spread = spread / 2 #absolute tc (transactional cost) per trade (position change +- 1)
half_spread
Out[70]:
7.500000000000001e-05
In [72]:
#creat proportional transaction cost
#What percentage of your money you lose per trading action (half spread) due to spread? this is what ptc neab
# You divide by mean_price to normalize the spread into a percentage of the asset’s value — just like we do when calculating returns.
ptc = half_spread / data.price.mean() #proportional tc per trade (position change +-1)
ptc

In [90]:
#counting how many trade taken
# 0 is no trade, 2 is trade which open and cancle the trade it twice action that mean we pay not half(which only one action) but two or full spread
#this why the trade count is 2 for every trade
#must remember: A complete trade (entry + exit) = two actions

#calculated real profit of strategy after trading cost calculated
#jadi strategy return itu == total pendapatan kotor - berapa kali aksi * persentase dari nilai yang hilang akibat aksi
#why not multiply by halfspread? karena ini adalah angka return maka harus dilakikan dengan return which mean ptc
#jika dikalikan dengan half_spread itu one unit spread bukan rata-rata simplify return 
data['strategy_net'] = data.strategy - data.trades * ptc
